Choose specific program

program = 'fasttree'
if (program=='fasttree') {
    all_models_performance = fasttree_all_models_performance
    final_models_performance = fasttree_final_models_performance %>% filter(analysis_type!='feature_standard_fasttree_boot_support')
    group_performance = fasttree_group_performance
    vi = fasttree_vi
    enriched_test = fasttree_enriched_test
    #validation_data = fasttree_validation_data
    
} else if (program=='iqtree') {
    all_models_performance = iqtree_all_models_performance
    final_models_performance = iqtree_final_models_performance
    group_performance = iqtree_group_performance
    vi = iqtree_vi
    enriched_test = iqtree_enriched_test
    #validation_data = iqtree_validation_data
} else if (program=='raxml') {
    all_models_performance = raxml_all_models_performance
    final_models_performance = raxml_final_models_performance
    group_performance = raxml_group_performance
    vi = raxml_vi
    enriched_test = raxml_enriched_test
    #validation_data = raxml_validation
}

IQTREE


summm_iqtree<- iqtree_enriched_test %>% group_by(tree_id) %>% summarise(mean_true = mean(true_binary_support), mean_pred = mean(prob_predictions), mean_bayes = mean(feature_aBayes_iqtree_support), mean_ultrafast = mean(bootstrap_support), mean_bayes_cal = mean(predictions_feature_aBayes_iqtree_support_only_boot),
                                                mean_alrt = mean(feature_aLRT_iqtree_support), mean_alrt_cal = mean(predictions_feature_aLRT_iqtree_support_only_boot))
                                                

bayes<-summm_iqtree%>% ggplot(aes(x=mean_true,y=mean_bayes))+geom_point(alpha = 1/3)+geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0,color = "green")+xlab("True proportion")+ylab("aBayes test")+theme(text = element_text(size = 11))

alrt<-summm_iqtree %>% ggplot(aes(x=mean_true,y=mean_alrt))+geom_point(alpha = 1/3)+geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0,color = "green")+xlab("True proportion")+ylab("aLRT test ")+theme(text = element_text(size = 11))

ultrafast<-summm_iqtree %>% ggplot(aes(x=mean_true,y=mean_ultrafast/100))+geom_point(alpha = 1/3)+geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0,color = "green")+xlab("True proportion")+ylab("Ultrafast\nbootstrap")+theme(text = element_text(size = 11))


pred_iqtree<-summm_iqtree  %>% ggplot(aes(x=mean_true,y=mean_pred))+geom_point(alpha = 1/3)+geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0,color = "green")+xlab("True proportion")+ylab("IQTREE\nmodel")+theme(text = element_text(size = 11))



iqtree_plot<-ggarrange(pred_iqtree,ultrafast,bayes,alrt, labels = c("A","B","C"),align = "h", nrow = 2, ncol = 2 )
iqtree_plot

FASTTREE

summm_fasttree<- fasttree_enriched_test %>% group_by(tree_id) %>% summarise(mean_true = mean(true_binary_support), mean_pred = mean(prob_predictions), mean_sh = mean(bootstrap_support))
                                                

pred_fasttree<-summm_fasttree  %>% ggplot(aes(x=mean_true,y=mean_pred))+geom_point(alpha = 1/3)+geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0,color = "green")+xlab("True proportion")+ylab("Fasttree\nmodel")+theme(text = element_text(size = 11))

sh<-summm_fasttree  %>% ggplot(aes(x=mean_true,y=mean_sh))+geom_point(alpha = 1/3)+geom_abline(slope=1, intercept = 0,color = "green")+xlab("True proportion")+ylab("SH test")+theme(text = element_text(size = 11))


fasttree_plot<-ggarrange(pred_fasttree,sh, labels = c("A","B"),align = "h", nrow = 1, ncol = 2 )
fasttree_plot

General performance IQTREE


out_path <-paste(prefix,"ML_results/","iqtree","/performance_text",".tsv", sep = "")

paper_performance_iqtree<-iqtree_final_models_performance  %>% filter (metric_type=='all_data') %>% dplyr::select (dataset,analysis_type,name,mcc_0.5,logloss, AUC,average_precision, tp_0.5, tn_0.5, fp_0.5, fn_0.5)  %>% arrange(dataset) %>% mutate (description = case_when(analysis_type == "full_standard" & name =="model_standard" ~ "all features", 
                                analysis_type == "fast_standard" & name =="model_standard" ~ "All features except NNI features",
                                analysis_type == "bootstrap_support" & name =="raw_only_boot" ~ "Raw ultrafast bootstrap support",
                                analysis_type == "bootstrap_support" & name =="only_boot" ~ "Calibrated ultrafast bootstrap support",
                                analysis_type == "bootstrap_support" & name =="inc_boot" ~ "All features+ ultrafast bootstrap support",
                                    analysis_type == "feature_aLRT_iqtree_support" & name =="raw_only_boot" ~ "Raw aLRT support",
                                analysis_type == "feature_aLRT_iqtree_support" & name =="only_boot" ~ "Calibrated aLRT support",
                                analysis_type == "feature_aLRT_iqtree_support" & name =="inc_boot" ~ "All features+ aLRT support",
                                                                    analysis_type == "feature_aBayes_iqtree_support" & name =="raw_only_boot" ~ "Raw aBayes support",
                                analysis_type == "feature_aBayes_iqtree_support" & name =="only_boot" ~ "Calibrated aBayes support",
                                analysis_type == "feature_aBayes_iqtree_support" & name =="inc_boot" ~ "All features+ aBayes support",
                                )) %>% mutate(TPR =`tp_0.5`/(`tp_0.5`+`fn_0.5`),TNR =`tn_0.5`/(`tn_0.5`+`fp_0.5`),FPR =`fp_0.5`/(`tn_0.5`+`fp_0.5`),FNR =`fn_0.5`/(`tp_0.5`+`fn_0.5`)) %>% dplyr::select (dataset, description,logloss, mcc_0.5,FPR,FNR, AUC,average_precision)  %>% arrange(dataset)

Results on test data

total_model_performance = rbind(paper_performance_iqtree %>% mutate(program='IQTREE'), paper_performance_fasttree %>% mutate(program='FastTree'), paper_performance_raxml %>% mutate(program='RAxML-NG')) %>% filter (dataset %in% c("test"), description %in% c("all features","Raw SH support","Raw aLRT support","Raw aBayes support","Raw bootstrap support","Raw ultrafast bootstrap support")) %>% mutate(Support = description) %>% rename(MCC = mcc_0.5)



mcc_plot<-total_model_performance %>% ggplot(aes(y=MCC, x = program, fill = Support))+geom_col(position = "dodge")
logloss_plot<-total_model_performance %>% ggplot(aes(y=logloss, x = program, fill = Support))+geom_col(position = "dodge")

Variable importance IQTREE

out_path <-paste(prefix,"ML_results/","iqtree","/vi_text",".tsv", sep = "")

  `...1` == "feature_min_ll_diff_opt=True_model_False"~ "Minimum log-likelihood difference between an NNI neighbor near the bipartition and current tree",

Confusion matrix

ggplotConfusionMatrix <- function(m){
  mytitle <- ""#paste("Accuracy", percent_format()(m$overall[1]))
                  # "Kappa", percent_format()(m$overall[2]))
  p <-
    ggplot(data = as.data.frame(m$table) ,
           aes(x = Reference, y = Prediction)) +
    geom_tile(aes(fill = log(Freq)), colour = "white") +
    scale_fill_gradient(low = "white", high = "steelblue") +
    geom_text(aes(x = Reference, y = Prediction, label = scales::comma(Freq))) +
    theme(legend.position = "none") +
    ggtitle(mytitle)+theme(text = element_text(size = 13))
  return(p)
}
conf_data<-iqtree_enriched_test %>% dplyr::select (prob_predictions, true_label) %>% mutate (pred_status = prob_predictions>0.5) 

obs<- factor(conf_data %>% pull (true_label))
pred<- factor(conf_data %>% pull (pred_status))


confusion_plot<-ggplotConfusionMatrix(confusionMatrix(data = pred, reference= obs))+theme(legend.position = "none")
